      "surface_id": "draw.canvas-grid",
      "title": "Draw canvas grid dots (guarded @outline-variant color source)",
      "chapter_section": "11.2",
      "status": "source-declared",
      "notes": "Only the grid-DOT COLOR is source-side: a guarded helper sources the @outline-variant token for the grid color instead of the DRAWGRID app-color-config value, inert under the native theme. The token_consumption.ordering block pins that the helper short-circuits to nothing under GetHighContrastMode() BEFORE resolving the Material color, so resolved high contrast keeps the native GetGridColor() path (HC wins). Grid GEOMETRY (document-unit GetGridCoarse()/GetGridFine() spacing vs. a fixed CSS cell), the procedural 3x3 corner-bitmap dot SHAPE, and the separate canvas base-fill (APPBACKGROUNDCOLOR) are explicitly out of this entry's scope and remain build-bound. Cross-module reach: viewobjectcontactofsdrpage.cxx is shared SdrView engine code, so the guarded recolor also reaches Writer/Calc/Base embedded draw grids and Impress grid-visible -- broader than the Draw-shell scope; flagged for product sign-off.",
      "owner_sources": [
        "svx/source/sdr/contact/viewobjectcontactofsdrpage.cxx"
      ],
      "owner_markers": [],
      "definition_parts": [],
      "status_model": null,
      "token_consumption": [
        {
          "source": "svx/source/sdr/contact/viewobjectcontactofsdrpage.cxx",
          "include": "<vcl/MaterialTokens.hxx>",
          "markers": [
            "VCL_FILE_WIDGET_THEME",
            "vcl::MaterialTokens::fromThemeDefinition",
            "findColor(\"outline-variant\")",
            "GetHighContrastMode()"
          ],
          "ordering": {
            "function": "lcl_getMaterialGridColor",
            "high_contrast_marker": "GetHighContrastMode()",
            "contiguous": "if (Application::GetSettings().GetStyleSettings().GetHighContrastMode()) return std::nullopt;"
          }
        }
      ],
      "disabled_policy": null,
      "runtime_verified": false
